commit.message:
readme: Add examples for biblio-cleanup-bibtex-function

Part of #37.
core: Rewrite --help-with-major-mode-1 to make results more readable
doi: Rename doi-insert-bibtex into biblio-doi-insert-bibtex

core: Bind p and n to selection-previous and selection-next

Closes GH-41.

Suggested-by: @mlemerre

Add test for new face

Check whether the face in biblio-selection-mode is actually the one we want.

Add new highlight face in biblio-selection-mode

Add a new face and set is as buffer-local default for hl-line-face.

core: Honor biblio-bibtex-use-autokey in doi-insert-bibtex (closes GH-34)

Suggested-by: @jowens

core: Add an option to generate custom BibTeX keys (closes GH-34)

Suggested-by: @jowens

core: Fontify the bibtex buffer before cleaning it up in -format-bibtex

bibtex-mode relies on fontification, so the current code caused errors: ‘Error
during redisplay: (internal--syntax-propertize 516) signaled (error "Font-lock
trying to use keywords before setting them up")’
dblp, doi: Remove redundant calls to -format-bibtex
core: Don't set bibtex-autokey-year-title-separator in --cleanup-bibtex

Change all URLs to https

Suggested-by: @m4lvin

all: Retrieve and display publication dates

Closes GH-30.

Suggested-by: @dschrempf

readme: Add more information about adding new actions

Closes #24.
tests: Escape '.' in argument to looking-at-p
core: Fix typos
readme: Document the new biblio-crossref user email setting

crossref, tests: Allow users to add a 'mailto' parameter to queries

Closes GH-27.

Suggested-By: @leezu
core: Strip properties of BibTeX strings
tests: Add missing IEEE cache
readme: Mention IEEE Xplore

biblio: Add an IEEE Xplore backend

Closes GH-16.

Suggested-by: @notuntoward
tests: Update to latest version of buttercup
all: Tweak wording of backend headers
arxiv: Use aref instead of elt

arxiv: parse year correctly

Fixes #9. Removes the helper function `biblio-arxiv--extract-year` in
favor of using `timezone-parse-date`. The tests for
`biblio-arxiv--extract-year` are also removed.
